    "en": {
      "title": "6 deaths and disappearances due to drowning",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "03 deaths and missing persons have been reported due to drowning accidents in three places of the island.",
        "Thus, a woman and a girl who were returning home from pre-school in Polpitiya, Hitinegama area had drowned and disappeared. Later, during a joint search operation by the police and local residents, the 5-year-old granddaughter and the 62-year-old grandmother were found and they died when they were admitted to Ginigathhena Hospital.",
        "Two people and a woman have gone missing after crossing the Kambulawa Oya in Akkarawatta, Nawalapitiya. The people who have drowned and disappeared are the residents of Katambulawa area, aged 36, 46, and 47 years.",
        "Meanwhile, police say that one of the three people who were walking home in the Hatton Montafair area slipped and fell into the Panmure lake and went missing. A resident of Hatton, Abosliwatta, has been missing for 24 years."
      ],
